cs.DC, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.ET 

This paper discusses the design of energy-efficient computing systems, specifically focusing on data centers and cloud computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper covers topics related to hardware, operating systems, and virtualization, which could fall under cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper also discusses energy efficiency, which could fall under cs.ET (Emerging Technologies).
